1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Robotics students often memorize transformations
without seeing what the symbols do.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:14,000
AxisLab turns equations into verified lessons
where students predict, manipulate, observe, and check.

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Six modules connect robot motion,
coordinate systems, orientation, velocity, and forces.

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:29,000
The direct robot demonstration is deterministic
and requires no external model call.

5
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Changing d1 translates along its joint axis,
while theta2 rotates the downstream chain.

6
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:45,000
The 3D model, DH table, matrices,
and end-effector position update together.

7
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:53,000
The RPY and Euler wrist can be rotated with the mouse
and controlled with three live angle sliders.

8
00:00:53,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Learners compare rotation conventions,
recover inverse angles, and inspect singularities.

9
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Coordinate, Jacobian, trajectory, and dynamics labs
use the same active-learning interface.

10
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Each lesson combines visible geometry,
equations, controls, and scored questions.

11
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Natural-language questions can request
a customized advanced robotics lesson.

12
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:33,000
The model proposes teaching intent,
difficulty, and bounded starting parameters.

13
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Deterministic code validates the result
and owns numerical answers and scoring.

14
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Generated code is never executed,
and provider failures activate reviewed fallback lessons.

15
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Codex helped analyze the system,
plan the architecture, and implement the learning modules.

16
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:07,000
It supported mathematical review, automated tests,
responsive design, debugging, and deployment migration.

17
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:17,000
[Replace this subtitle with the exact, verified way
GPT-5.6 contributed to the final project.]

18
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Twenty-one backend tests and twenty frontend tests
verify the current implementation.

19
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:34,000
The public HTTPS demo requires no account,
and direct lessons remain available without an AI provider.

20
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:43,000
AxisLab makes difficult robotics mathematics
visible, interactive, and verifiable.

21
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:51,000
It is a safer foundation for active,
AI-assisted robotics education.
